# Universal Coding Rulebook - Pointer

This project follows the universal rulebook in `vibeCodingRules/AGENTS.md` (path is machine-specific; see `cursor-sync.md`).

Before any code change, the agent MUST:

1. Read `AGENTS.md` to determine which rule files apply to the task.
2. Run `feature-discovery.md` grilling (3-5 questions) unless a skip trigger fires.
3. Open every REQUIRED file from the routing matrix and skim mandatory sections.
4. Apply the per-edit checklist (sections A-H) to every line touched.
5. Sync `cursor/*.mdc` after any rule/cursor change (`cursor-sync.md`).

**Universal only:** Product domains and stack overrides live in project `docs/` - not in the rulebook.

Hard bans: see `AGENTS.md` § Hard Bans.
